 created_at



 ‚úÖ Owner Responsibilities (Business View)
 Register
 Login
 Create hostel
 Update hostel details
 View dashboard stats
 Add tenants
 Vacate tenants
 View collections


CREATE TABLE owner (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    mobile VARCHAR(15) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    email VARCHAR(150) UNIQUE,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);






CREATE TABLE hostel (
    id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    owner_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
    name VARCHAR(150) NOT NULL,
    total_beds INT NOT NULL,
    monthly_fee NUMERIC(10,2),
    maintenance_fee NUMERIC(10,2),
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

 CREATE TABLE bed (
     id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
     hostel_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
     bed_number VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
     status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL
 );

 Good thinking. This is exactly how a **system architect** approaches a product:
 define **actors ‚Üí modules ‚Üí actions ‚Üí flows** before coding.

 Below is a **clean product scope** for your hostel management SaaS so you **don‚Äôt go out of track**.

 ---

 # 1Ô∏è‚É£ OWNER MODULE (Hostel Owner Actions)

 ### Account & Profile

 Owner can:

 * Register account
 * Login
 * Update profile
 * Change password
 * Logout

 ---

 ### Hostel Management

 Owner can:

 * Create hostel
 * Update hostel details
 * Delete hostel
 * View hostel dashboard

 Hostel details:
 * hostel name
 * address
 * number of beds
 * default fee (optional)

 ---

 ### Bed Management

 Owner can:

 * View all beds
 * Increase bed count
 * Decrease bed count (only if beds are AVAILABLE)
 * Rename beds
 * Set default bed price
 * Set maintenance fee

 Bed states:

 ```
 AVAILABLE
 RESERVED
 OCCUPIED
 MAINTENANCE
 ```

 ---

 ### Tenant Onboarding

 Owner can:

 * Select bed
 * Enter tenant basic details:

   * name
   * mobile
   * negotiated monthly fee
   * maintenance fee
   * advance amount

 System will:

 ```
 Generate onboarding token
 ‚Üì
 Send WhatsApp link
 ```

 Owner can also:

 * Resend onboarding link
 * Cancel onboarding request

 ---

 ### Tenant Management

 Owner can:

 * View all tenants
 * View tenant profile
 * Edit tenant details
 * See tenant payment history
 * See tenant due amount
 * Vacate tenant

 When tenant vacates:

 ```
 BedAllocation END
 ‚Üì
 Advance refund calculation
 ‚Üì
 Bed becomes AVAILABLE
 ```

 ---

 ### Payments & Billing

 Owner can:

 * View monthly collection
 * View pending payments
 * View payment history
 * View advance balances
 * Download receipts
 * Record offline payments (optional)

 ---

 ### Monthly Billing

 Every month system will:

 ```
 Generate new monthly bill
 ‚Üì
 Send reminder
 ```

 Owner can:

 * mark payment received
 * add late fee
 * extend due date

 ---

 ### Notifications

 Owner receives:

 * payment success alerts
 * tenant registration alerts
 * vacancy alerts
 * due alerts

 ---

 ### Dashboard

 Owner dashboard shows:

 * total beds
 * occupied beds
 * available beds
 * tenants
 * monthly revenue
 * pending payments
 * advance balances

 ---

 # 2Ô∏è‚É£ TENANT MODULE

 ### Onboarding

 Tenant receives WhatsApp link.

 Tenant can:

 * open onboarding link
 * see prefilled details
 * fill profile details
 * upload ID proof (optional)
 * pay advance + monthly fee

 After payment:

 ```
 Tenant status ‚Üí ACTIVE
 Bed ‚Üí OCCUPIED
 ```

 ---

 ### Tenant Profile

 Tenant can:

 * update profile
 * update email
 * upload documents
 * update emergency contact

 ---

 ### Payments

 Tenant can:

 * pay monthly fee
 * pay advance
 * see payment history
 * download receipts

 Payment methods:

 ```
 UPI
 PhonePe
 Google Pay
 Card
 ```

 ---

 ### Notifications

 Tenant receives:

 * payment reminders
 * payment success confirmation
 * upcoming due reminder
 * hostel announcements

 ---

 ### Tenant Dashboard

 Tenant can see:

 * bed details
 * rent amount
 * due amount
 * payment history
 * advance balance

 ---

 # 3Ô∏è‚É£ BED MODULE

 Bed contains:

 * bedId
 * hostelId
 * bedName
 * bedNumber
 * status

 Statuses:

 ```
 AVAILABLE
 RESERVED
 OCCUPIED
 MAINTENANCE
 ```

 Actions:

 Owner can:

 * rename bed
 * change bed price
 * mark bed under maintenance
 * release bed

 ---

 # 4Ô∏è‚É£ BED ALLOCATION MODULE

 Represents **tenant stay record**.

 Fields:

 ```
 tenantId
 bedId
 agreedMonthlyFee
 maintenanceFee
 advancePaid
 startDate
 endDate
 status
 ```

 Statuses:

 ```
 PENDING
 ACTIVE
 ENDED
 ```

 Actions:

 * allocate bed
 * end allocation
 * transfer tenant to another bed

 ---

 # 5Ô∏è‚É£ PAYMENT MODULE

 Types:

 ```
 ADVANCE_PAYMENT
 MONTHLY_RENT
 MAINTENANCE_FEE
 LATE_FEE
 REFUND
 ```

 Actions:

 * create payment
 * record payment
 * payment webhook handling
 * refund advance

 ---

 # 6Ô∏è‚É£ BILLING MODULE

 Monthly billing process:

 ```
 1st of month
 ‚Üì
 Generate monthly invoice
 ‚Üì
 Send WhatsApp reminder
 ‚Üì
 Due date = 5th
 ‚Üì
 Late fee after due date
 ```

 ---

 # 7Ô∏è‚É£ REMINDER SYSTEM

 Automatic reminders:

 * 3 days before due
 * due day
 * overdue reminder

 Channels:

 ```
 WhatsApp
 SMS
 Email
 ```

 ---

 # 8Ô∏è‚É£ VACATE TENANT FLOW

 Owner selects **vacate tenant**

 System will:

 ```
 calculate pending dues
 ‚Üì
 calculate advance refund
 ‚Üì
 close BedAllocation
 ‚Üì
 Bed status ‚Üí AVAILABLE
 ‚Üì
 tenant status ‚Üí VACATED
 ```

 ---

 # 9Ô∏è‚É£ REPORTS MODULE

 Owner can see:

 * monthly revenue report
 * payment collection report
 * pending dues report
 * occupancy report

 ---

 # üîü ADMIN MODULE (Later)

 Admin can:

 * manage owners
 * suspend accounts
 * view system metrics
 * manage subscriptions

 ---

